The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, April 19, 2004 				 Informer assailants arrested
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Four criminals, who had shot a youth for tipping off the police, were arrested from different areas of east Calcutta over the weekend. Police recovered three firearms and nine rounds of cartridges from them.																								A.B. Majumdar, officer-in-charge of Entally police station, said Mohammad Raja, alias Kana Gabbar, and three associates  Shyamal, Bablu and Sanju  had fired at Mohammad Naushad from close range on April 15. They assembled in front of Naushads house in Entally and Shyamal called him out. The moment Naushad appeared, Gabbar whipped out a gun and pulled the trigger, said Majumdar. Naushad had a narrow escape as the bullet grazed his ribs.																								Police launched a hunt for the four men.We were told late on Friday that a rendezvous was lined up in south Calcutta. With the help of Shakespeare Sarani police station, a joint raid netted Gabbar, Shyamal and Bablu, said sub-inspector Shantanu Majumdar of Entally police station.																								Early on Saturday, another round of raids led by sub-inspector P. K. Ghosal was conducted in the Motijhil area and Sanju was nabbed. A search of the houses of all the arrested men yielded the arms and bullets.																								Police said Naushad was attacked as the gangsters suspected him of working as an informer. They feared his tips could lead to their arrest, added an official of Entally police station.
